verses.roman:
tumi more dile bahu amūlya ratana
mora kichu dite nāhi, diluṅ āliṅgana

synonyms: tumi—you; more—unto Me; dile—delivered; bahu—various; amūlya—incalculable; ratana—gems; mora—of Me; kichu—anything; dite—to give; nāhi—there is not; diluṅ—I give; āliṅgana—embracing.
translation: Upon hearing the verses recited by the King, Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu said, "You have given Me invaluable gems, but I have nothing to give you in return. Therefore I am simply embracing you."
